Equine viral arteritis, United Kingdom
--------------------------------------
Information received on 17 Dec 2010 from Dr Nigel Gibbens, Chief
Veterinary Officer, Department for Environment, Food and Rural
Affairs, Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, London,
United Kingdom

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 1
Start date 15 Sep 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 08 Dec 2010
Report date 17 Dec 2010
Date submitted to OIE 17 Dec 2010
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence 19 Nov 2010
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Equine arteritis virus
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports - Immediate notification (09 Dec 2010); Follow-up
report No. 1 (17 Dec 2010)

Outbreaks: There are no new outbreaks in this report

Epidemiology - Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection -
Legal movement of animals

Epidemiological comments: The epidemiological inquiry has now been
completed without being able to determine a credible source of
infection within Great Britain. According to the inquiry no evidence
has been found of the stallion having been used for any breeding
activity while in Great Britain. There is no evidence of infection in
any in-contact horses. The stallion remains under restriction.

Control measures - Measures applied: Quarantine; Disinfection of
infected premises/establishment(s); No vaccination; No treatment of
affected animals

Measures to be applied - No other measures

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

